Uses of Package
cbf.engine

  • Packages that use cbf.engine 
    Package Description
    cbf.engine
    Classes to run component based test cases, to track the runtime status of execution, and to encapsulate runtime exception handling, test failures and recovery.
    cbf.harness
    Classes necessary to initialize the framework configurations.
    cbf.model
    Provides all the core interfaces related to framework.
    cbfx.factory.report
    Manages different types of reporting like excel, html, alm, email etc.
    cbfx.testng
    Provides classes for parallel/cross browser execution.
  • Classes in cbf.engine used by cbf.engine 
    Class and Description
    MultiTestRunner 
    MultiTestRunner.Handler 
    ParameterAccess
    Implements interface TestResultTracker.Reporter and provides access to parameters
    TestResult
    Defines the result object structure with the details like entityType (which can be TESTSUITE, TESTCASE, ITERATION, TESTSTEP etc), entityName, actual value of the entity (like tc name, iter name, step name etc), entityDetails, actual entity object which gives complete details of entity, finalRsType, final result of the executed entity startTime, execution start time finishTime, execution finish time msRsType, most significant result msDetails, most significant result's details
    TestResult.EntityType
    Defines fixed set of entity types used
    TestResult.ResultType
    Defines set of result types used
    TestResultTracker
    Adds multiple reporters enabled in configuration and tracks execution results for reporting
    TestResultTracker.Observer
    Logs execution events with details
    TestResultTracker.Trackable
    Tracks runtime result for different entity types
    TestRunner
    Class contains the entire execution logic.
